Here are the MSTest patterns for each scenario:

## 1. Windows-only tests — conditional skip

```csharp
[TestMethod]
[OSCondition(OperatingSystem.Windows)] // MSTest v3+ with TestPlatform conditions
public void Registry_ReadsValue_Successfully() { ... }

// Or manually:
[TestMethod]
public void Registry_ReadsValue_Successfully()
{
    if (!OperatingSystem.IsWindows())
        Assert.Inconclusive("Requires Windows.");
    // ...
}
```

## 2. Skip in CI (requires local GPU)

```csharp
[TestMethod]
public void Render_WithGpu_ProducesFrame()
{
    if (Environment.GetEnvironmentVariable("CI") is not null)
        Assert.Inconclusive("Skipped in CI — requires local GPU.");
    // ...
}
```

Or define a custom attribute:

```csharp
[AttributeUsage(AttributeTargets.Method)]
public class RequiresGpuAttribute : Attribute, ITestDataSource { ... }
// Simpler: use a helper method or test category + filter

[TestMethod]
[TestCategory("RequiresGpu")]
public void Render_WithGpu_ProducesFrame() { ... }
```

Then exclude in CI: `dotnet test --filter "TestCategory!=RequiresGpu"`

## 3. Flaky external API — retry with `[Timeout]` + custom retry

```csharp
[TestMethod]
[Timeout(10000)] // fail-safe timeout
[DataRow(1)]
[DataRow(2)]
[DataRow(3)] // poor-man's retry via rows (not ideal)
public void Weather_Returns200(int _attempt) { ... }
```

Better approach — use `[RetryAttribute]` (MSTest v3.8+):

```csharp
[TestMethod]
[Retry(3)] // retries up to 3 times on failure
public void WeatherApi_ReturnsCurrentTemperature() { ... }
```

## 4. Cleanup even on failure — use `[TestCleanup]` or `try/finally`

```csharp
private string? _tempFile;

[TestInitialize]
public void Setup()
{
    _tempFile = Path.GetTempFileName();
}

[TestCleanup]
public void Cleanup()
{
    if (_tempFile is not null && File.Exists(_tempFile))
        File.Delete(_tempFile);
}

[TestMethod]
public void Export_WritesToTempFile()
{
    File.WriteAllText(_tempFile!, "data");
    // assert...
}
```

`[TestCleanup]` runs **regardless of pass/fail**, making it the idiomatic choice for resource teardown.

---

**Summary of tools:**

| Scenario | Mechanism |
|----------|-----------|
| OS-specific | `Assert.Inconclusive()` or `[OSCondition]` |
| Skip in CI | `[TestCategory]` + filter, or env-var check |
| Flaky/retry | `[Retry(n)]` (MSTest v3.8+) |
| Guaranteed cleanup | `[TestCleanup]` method |
